The paper deals with algorithms and data structures for solving a specific problem in planar digraphs, which involves computing max st-flow values and min cut-sets. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and game theory (cs.GT). However, since the paper focuses primarily on algorithmic techniques and time complexity analysis, cs.DS and cs.CG are the most likely sub-categories. The use of lower bounds and the mention of previous results also suggest that cs.DM and cs.NA are possible sub-categories. The mention of implications for all-pairs max st-flow values and the distinction from the undirected case suggest that cs.GT is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
